Ten people were killed in Thailand when a van  carrying a group of school teachers was crushed in a head-on smash with a  truck, press reports said Sunday.
Nine teachers on their way to a colleagues's farewell dinner were among  the dead, leaving their school in the Ubon Ratchathani province, 629  kilometers (390 miles) northeast of Bangkok, with only one teacher, the  reports said.
Three passengers from the six-wheel truck were in critical condition, the  Daily News said.
